    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>London</placeName>. <date>Jany. 24<hi rend="sup"
                        >Th</hi> 5614/1854</date></p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I have long proposed to have this pleasure if<lb/> only to inform
                you of <persName>Mrs. Nathan</persName> and myself not having forgotten you, but
                apart from<lb/> the disarrangement which moving from one country to another
                occasions, and the unfixed<lb/> habits it creates, my poor wife has, I regret to say
                been an invalid for the last 11 weeks.<lb/> Her sufferings have been so severe, as
                to have debarred me from communicating with<lb/> even an old friend like you. I
                wished particularly to send you my address, having<lb/> noticed in the slip round
                the Occident directed to me, and for which thoughtful<lb/> act I kindly thank you,
                your request to <persName>Mrs Joel</persName> to ascertain my whereabouts<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs. N.</persName> is I am happy to say mending, tho' very slowly. Her
                situation in a city<lb/> where friends are separated by such great distances as to
                render a friendly visit<lb/> a toil, has confined me to the house to relieve the
                tediousness of her solitude, so that<lb/> I know little or nothing of Jewish
                affairs, and the pending controversy between<lb/> the Board of deputies and the
                country congregations, the only subject I suppose<lb/> about which you care to know
                I have met with <persName>Dr. Adler</persName> twice, and in my<lb/> next will offer
                a few observations respecting him and the Jews generally.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It was my intention to visit <placeName>America</placeName> on my
                way to <placeName>Europe</placeName>, but<lb/> the steamers would have taken us
                first to <placeName>Aspinwall</placeName>, and I feared going<lb/> to the
                    <placeName>Isthmus</placeName> even for a few days after the experience I had of
                it last<lb/>
                <date>January</date>. I wished especially to see <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                once more for the sake<lb/> of seeing old friends again, and ascertaining also
                whether it would have<lb/> suited us to live there. “Man denkt aber Gott lenkt.”
                Convey however to our numerous<lb/> friends there our warmest remembrances, and our
                hopes that we may yet<lb/> meet again in this life. How is your Bible getting on?
                When will it be ready?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Did the translation I lent you of the Book of
                    <persName>Job</persName> prove of any service, in opening<lb/> up new readings
                &amp;c? What do you think of <persName>Gutheim's</persName> accepting my late
                situation<lb/> after resigning his former one on the plea of intention of quitting
                the ministry alto-<lb/>gether? Rather strange the whole proceeding. God be with you
                is the united<lb/> wish of <persName>Mrs. N</persName> and myself, and hoping this
                will meet you and all friends<lb/> in good health</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your's as of old</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">M N Nathan</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Direct to me care of <persName>Messrs Carvalho &amp; Delgado</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>8 ½ Cross St.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Finsbury</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>London</placeName>.</p>
        </body>
